    "title": {
        "rendered": "ResponsiveWrapper"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>A wrapper component that maintains its aspect ratio when resized.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">import { ResponsiveWrapper } from '@wordpress/components';\n\nconst MyResponsiveWrapper = () =&gt; (\n    &lt;ResponsiveWrapper naturalWidth={ 2000 } naturalHeight={ 680 }&gt;\n        &lt;img\n            src=\"https://s.w.org/style/images/about/WordPress-logotype-standard.png\"\n            alt=\"WordPress\"\n        /&gt;\n    &lt;/ResponsiveWrapper&gt;\n);\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Usage with <code>SVG</code> elements</h3>\n<p>When passing an <code>SVG</code> element as the <code>&lt;ResponsiveWrapper /&gt;</code>&#8216;s child, make sure that it has the <code>viewbox</code> and the <code>preserveAspectRatio</code> set.</p>\n<p>When dealing with SVGs, it may not be possible to derive its <code>naturalWidth</code> and <code>naturalHeight</code> and therefore passing them as propertied to <code>&lt;ResponsiveWrapper /&gt;</code>. In this case, the SVG simply keeps scaling up to fill its container, unless the <code>height</code> and <code>width</code> attributes are specified.</p>\n<h2>Props</h2>\n<h3><code>children</code>: <code>React.ReactElement</code></h3>\n<p>The element to wrap.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: Yes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><code>isInline</code>: <code>boolean</code></h3>\n<p>If true, the wrapper will be <code>span</code> instead of <code>div</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: No</li>\n<li>Default: <code>false</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><code>naturalHeight</code>: <code>number</code></h3>\n<p>The intrinsic height of the element to wrap. Will be used to determine the aspect ratio.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: No</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><code>naturalWidth</code>: <code>number</code></h3>\n<p>The intrinsic width of the element to wrap. Will be used to determine the aspect ratio.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Required: No</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
